Then when we were really apart from each other like if he went back to brunei and when i was interning, we text more often so in the beginning of mco i thought it was good we have some time apart because on some days since we see each other so much, we got annoyed at each other

Can think outside the box. Space now can be turned to co working spaces. Entrepreneurs need an address to run their businesses, right? I think MCO really pushed all of us to think creatively and be more innovative.

Ours is 10% at office the rest effectively WFH. We’ve started a WFH policy even before MCO. But once a week. But there’s flexibility in working hours (clock in clock out) too all along. Just that IT infrastructure wasn’t as enhanced as during MCO now. After this WFH is a norm.

I also find myself more productive and have zoom/Webex calls only for important discussions that need immediate attention. Otherwise can be resolved by emails. I think what I’m hoping for after MCO is this flexibility that works for most of us.

10. Eat healthily Yaa i know during this mco. Many of us stay at home and also college. For those who stay at home please control your food intake. Even if your mom cooked your fav food. For those who stay at college do take breakfast lunch on time and avoid junk food.

3. Stay away from your phone It really tempting to spend hours a day on your phone especially when there's not much else to do & we don't have to go anywhere during this MCO. There is few things to limit your phone time and stay focused on your work. - put your phone away
The average adult should get between 7 to 9 hours of sleep each day. Reset your regular sleep schedule. In MCO i see there many of us start sleep from 1am. STOP scrolling sosial media at night .
